&lt;p&gt;As artificial intelligence (AI) systems, particularly large language models (LLMs), become integral to cybersecurity frameworks, they offer innovative solutions while introducing novel vulnerabilities. This article explores prompt-based threats, LLM-specific attack vectors, broader cybersecurity concepts in the context of AI, and essential governance and defense tools, alongside emerging trends and considerations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
